title: Les Misérables, Vol. 2
creator: Victor Hugo
description: LibriVox recording of Les Misérables, Vol. 1, by Victor Hugo. Read by Librivox Volunteers. An ex-convict breaks parole and starts a new life as a righteous man, but is pursued by a police inspector. Along the way, the ex-convict joins a revolution, adopts a daughter, and beats people up. Hooray. (Summary by smileyman457) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B Part 1 (188MB) Download M4B Part 2 (164MB)
